          <name xml:lang="en">price</name>
          <unitName xml:lang="en">EUR2005</unitName>
          <comment xml:lang="en">Calculated value based on data from the United Nations Commodity Trade Statistics Database (http://data.un.org/Data.aspx?q=natural+gas&amp;d=ComTrade&amp;f=_l1Code%3a28%3bcmdCode%3a270900; accessed 12 October 2023). UN comtrade category: 270900 Oils; petroleum oils and oils obtained from bituminous minerals, crude. An average for 2019-2021 was used and adjusted for inflation to the year 2005. The average price of imports and exports into the five main markets (EU, US, JP and CN) was determined.  For comparison, the reference crude quality Brent had an average price of US$(2021) 59.9 per barrel according to bp (2022), or EUR2005 0.317 per kg, in the same period.</comment>
